  "description": "Oracle Financials is the financial management component of Oracle\u0026rsquo;s enterprise resource planning suite. The product has evolved through several generations — Oracle E-Business Suite and JD Edwards were the predecessors — and is now delivered as Oracle Cloud ERP (also called Oracle Fusion Cloud). Oracle competes directly with SAP for large enterprise deployments.\n¶What It Does Oracle Financials covers general ledger, accounts payable, accounts receivable, fixed assets, cash management, expense management, financial consolidation, and intercompany accounting. It integrates with Oracle\u0026rsquo;s broader ERP modules for procurement, project management, supply chain, and human capital management. Oracle also provides analytics and reporting tools built on its own database technology.\n",
